When one post on the zeronet site which does not feature edit button and want to edit or remove the comment, here is what to do:

1. open that site and mouse drag & drop the (0) corner button to the left to open menu
2. scroll down to find IDENTITY ADDRESS and copy it
3. scroll up and click "OPEN SITE DIRECTORY" (or open the site directory manually zeronet/data/siteaddress/)
4. once you are in that directory, go to subdirectory data/users/YOURIDENTITYADDRESS/ and check content.json and data.json files
5. you will find your text which you want to edit or delete.

Before you do any modification, copy all the text in that file into clipboard (memory) and paste it to a safe place so you can restore if something go wrong!!

**A) DELETING**

Regarding deleting, here is example part of the data.json content:

```{
	"file": {},
	"comment": {
		"123456_abcdefgh": [
			{
				"body": "your comment text 1",
				"date_added": 123456
			},
			{
				"body": "your comment text 2",
				"date_added": 123456
			},
			{
				"body": "your comment text 3",
				"date_added": 123456
			}
		]
	}
}```

when you want to delete comment "your comment text 2". you will remove:
```
			{
				"body": "your comment text 2",
				"date_added": 123456
			},
```
when you want to delete "your comment text 3", you will remove:
```
			{
				"body": "your comment text 3",
				"date_added": 123456
			}
```

Do you see the diference? comment 3 block of code does NOT end by comma "," symbol, because it is last block of code in comments section. This is important to know, because if you remove last block of code (comment 3), you have to adjust previous block code by removing ending comma "," from it turning:

```
{
	"file": {},
	"comment": {
		"123456_abcdefgh": [
			{
				"body": "your comment text 1",
				"date_added": 123456
			},
			{
				"body": "your comment text 2",
				"date_added": 123456
			},
			{
				"body": "your comment text 3",
				"date_added": 123456
			}
		]
	}
}
```

into:

```
{
	"file": {},
	"comment": {
		"123456_abcdefgh": [
			{
				"body": "your comment text 1",
				"date_added": 123456
			},
			{
				"body": "your comment text 2",
				"date_added": 123456
			}
		]
	}
}
```
(in short: making sure that after last "block" of code is not a comma ,)

**B) EDITING**

deleting of the comment/post is hard to explain, but editing is simple, just edit the comment text between the quotation marks. Make sure not to add any " into the text, because it may break the code i guess.

6 . Save the file and go back to the site where you do some action like a upvoting or adding new comment. Once you do that zeronet should show that it published content to several peers. It means the content.json and data.json files you have eddited should have been signed and published (including your modifications) to other peers. The modification should be visible also for you (maybe after reloading page, or rebuilding database from within site menu?).

