> [htgozn](#comment_96_1J58Rie679DVSuKB1iDyFFTbzmaMaY2bt2): Clone the site, explain what happened, become the new owner.

when i seen board with low space limit, i sometimes asked admin if he consider **to raise the users's limit** (increase user limit/quota on ZeroTalk clone) by editing ZeroNet/data/yoursiteaddress/data/users/content.json

replace:
  "permission_rules": {
   ".*": {
    "files_allowed": "data.json",
    "max_size": 20000
   },

by:
  "permission_rules": {
   ".*": {
    "files_allowed": "data.json",
    "max_size": 3000000
   },

3 000 000 is 3MB, default value for zerotalk is 20 KB (20000) at a time of writing.

After saving the content.json file, publish your modification by:
- going to your site, opening its (0) menu (swipe the top right button by the mouse to the left)
- scroll the menu to the bottom, where under "This is my site" section is option "Content publishing" where you click "data/users/content.json" and "Sign and publish".

