You can increase this limit for your clonned zerotalk site when you edit content.json from your site's users directory: (ZeroBundle/ZeroNet/data/YourSiteAddress/data/users/content.json)
I have there following:

  "permission_rules": {
   ".*": {
    "files_allowed": "data.json",
    "max_size": 1000000
   },
   "bitid/.*@zeroid.bit": {"max_size": 4000000},
   "bitmsg/.*@zeroid.bit": {"max_size": 1500000}
  },

in your case, you just need to replace the numeric values by other value, 20000 = 20kilobytes i think, one million is 1megabyte quota i guess. So replace 20000 by some higher value, save file, and then open your site ( 0 ) menu, on the bottom of the menu select data/users/content.json and sign and publish changes. I may be wrong.

If someone exhausting quota, he sees the message "You are running out of your allowed space, please contact" ...
You can find this in your index.html and update here your e-mail address, so they can contact you to raise the quota. But if you upgrade the site later to match newest  ZeroTalk features, you will probably loose all these modifications :-/

